            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJust%20when%20things%20looked%20the%20darkest%20for%20David%2C%20God%20was%20actually%20giving%20him%20the%20breakthrough.%20At%20Ziklag%2C%20David%20faced%20the%20lowest%20point%20in%20his%20life%2C%20for%20he%20lost%20his%20entire%20family%20in%20one%20day.%20After%20this%20tragedy%2C%20even%20his%20best%20friends%20were%20ready%20to%20stone%20him.%20Because%20he%20found%20strength%20in%20the%20Lord%2C%20however%2C%20God%20turned%20the%20whole%20situation%20around.%20%20%22David%20got%20back%20everything%20the%20Amalekites%20had%20taken%2C%20and%20he%20rescued%20his%20two%20wives.%20Nothing%20was%20missing%3A%20small%20or%20great%2C%20son%20or%20daughter%2C%20nor%20anything%20else%20that%20had%20been%20taken.%20David%20brought%20everything%20back%22%20(1%20Samuel%2030%3A18-19).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESomeone%20has%20pointed%20out%20that%20at%20Ziklag%20David%20was%20only%20seventy-two%20hours%20away%20from%20a%20miracle.%20Unknown%20to%20him%2C%20all%20the%20years%20of%20his%20running%20from%20Saul%20were%20about%20to%20come%20to%20an%20end.%20The%20test%20was%20almost%20over%2C%20but%20the%20final%20part%20of%20the%20test%20was%20the%20hardest.%20But%20afterward%2C%20not%20only%20did%20David%20recover%20everything%2C%20but%20he%20also%20gained%20a%20tremendous%20amount%20of%20wealth.%20He%20used%20that%20wealth%20to%20spread%20goodwill%20throughout%20Judah%2C%20and%20this%20initiated%20the%20process%20of%20his%20becoming%20king%20of%20Judah.%20What%20a%20turnabout%20from%20the%20deep%20depression%20of%20Ziklag!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYou%20may%20think%20you%20have%20waited%20forever%2C%20but%20you%20may%20be%20only%20sev-enty-two%20hours%20from%20your%20miracle.%20%22When%20Job%20prayed%20for%20his%20friends%2C%20the%20Lord%20restored%20his%20fortunes.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Lord%20gave%20him%20twice%20as%20much%20as%20before%22%20(Job%2042%3A10).%20Wait%20for%20God%20to%20turn%20your%20darkness%20into%20glorious%20light!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
