            "api_nlt_to_ref": "1Sam.29:1-31:13",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Samuel%2029%3A1-31%3A13%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Philistines%20Reject%20David%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20entire%20Philistine%20army%20now%20mobilized%20at%20Aphek%2C%20and%20the%20Israelites%20camped%20at%20the%20spring%20in%20Jezreel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_2%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20the%20Philistine%20rulers%20were%20leading%20out%20their%20troops%20in%20groups%20of%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%2C%20David%20and%20his%20men%20marched%20at%20the%20rear%20with%20King%20Achish.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20Philistine%20commanders%20demanded%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20are%20these%20Hebrews%20doing%20here%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EAnd%20Achish%20told%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20David%2C%20the%20servant%20of%20King%20Saul%20of%20Israel.%20He%26%23x2019%3Bs%20been%20with%20me%20for%20years%2C%20and%20I%26%23x2019%3Bve%20never%20found%20a%20single%20fault%20in%20him%20from%20the%20day%20he%20arrived%20until%20today.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_4%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20Philistine%20commanders%20were%20angry.%20%26%23x201C%3BSend%20him%20back%20to%20the%20town%20you%26%23x2019%3Bve%20given%20him!%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20demanded.%20%26%23x201C%3BHe%20can%26%23x2019%3Bt%20go%20into%20the%20battle%20with%20us.%20What%20if%20he%20turns%20against%20us%20in%20battle%20and%20becomes%20our%20adversary%3F%20Is%20there%20any%20better%20way%20for%20him%20to%20reconcile%20himself%20with%20his%20master%20than%20by%20handing%20our%20heads%20over%20to%20him%3F%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EIsn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20this%20the%20same%20David%20about%20whom%20the%20women%20of%20Israel%20sing%20in%20their%20dances%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x2018%3BSaul%20has%20killed%20his%20thousands%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20David%20his%20ten%20thousands%26%23x2019%3B%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_6%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Achish%20finally%20summoned%20David%20and%20said%20to%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20swear%20by%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20that%20you%20have%20been%20a%20trustworthy%20ally.%20I%20think%20you%20should%20go%20with%20me%20into%20battle%2C%20for%20I%26%23x2019%3Bve%20never%20found%20a%20single%20flaw%20in%20you%20from%20the%20day%20you%20arrived%20until%20today.%20But%20the%20other%20Philistine%20rulers%20won%26%23x2019%3Bt%20hear%20of%20it.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_7%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EPlease%20don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20upset%20them%2C%20but%20go%20back%20quietly.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_8%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20have%20I%20done%20to%20deserve%20this%20treatment%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20David%20demanded.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20have%20you%20ever%20found%20in%20your%20servant%2C%20that%20I%20can%26%23x2019%3Bt%20go%20and%20fight%20the%20enemies%20of%20my%20lord%20the%20king%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_9%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Achish%20insisted%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BAs%20far%20as%20I%26%23x2019%3Bm%20concerned%2C%20you%26%23x2019%3Bre%20as%20perfect%20as%20an%20angel%20of%20God.%20But%20the%20Philistine%20commanders%20are%20afraid%20to%20have%20you%20with%20them%20in%20the%20battle.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_10%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20get%20up%20early%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20and%20leave%20with%20your%20men%20as%20soon%20as%20it%20gets%20light.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_29_11%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2229%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%20and%20his%20men%20headed%20back%20into%20the%20land%20of%20the%20Philistines%2C%20while%20the%20Philistine%20army%20went%20on%20to%20Jezreel.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Destroys%20the%20Amalekites%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThree%20days%20later%2C%20when%20David%20and%20his%20men%20arrived%20home%20at%20their%20town%20of%20Ziklag%2C%20they%20found%20that%20the%20Amalekites%20had%20made%20a%20raid%20into%20the%20Negev%20and%20Ziklag%3B%20they%20had%20crushed%20Ziklag%20and%20burned%20it%20to%20the%20ground.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_2%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20had%20carried%20off%20the%20women%20and%20children%20and%20everyone%20else%20but%20without%20killing%20anyone.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20David%20and%20his%20men%20saw%20the%20ruins%20and%20realized%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20their%20families%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_4%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3Ethey%20wept%20until%20they%20could%20weep%20no%20more.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%26%23x2019%3Bs%20two%20wives%2C%20Ahinoam%20from%20Jezreel%20and%20Abigail%2C%20the%20widow%20of%20Nabal%20from%20Carmel%2C%20were%20among%20those%20captured.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_6%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20was%20now%20in%20great%20danger%20because%20all%20his%20men%20were%20very%20bitter%20about%20losing%20their%20sons%20and%20daughters%2C%20and%20they%20began%20to%20talk%20of%20stoning%20him.%20But%20David%20found%20strength%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_7%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20said%20to%20Abiathar%20the%20priest%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BBring%20me%20the%20ephod!%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20Abiathar%20brought%20it.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_8%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20David%20asked%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BShould%20I%20chase%20after%20this%20band%20of%20raiders%3F%20Will%20I%20catch%20them%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EAnd%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20told%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20go%20after%20them.%20You%20will%20surely%20recover%20everything%20that%20was%20taken%20from%20you!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_9%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%20and%20his%20600%26%23xA0%3Bmen%20set%20out%2C%20and%20they%20came%20to%20the%20brook%20Besor.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_10%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20200%26%23xA0%3Bof%20the%20men%20were%20too%20exhausted%20to%20cross%20the%20brook%2C%20so%20David%20continued%20the%20pursuit%20with%20400%26%23xA0%3Bmen.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_11%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EAlong%20the%20way%20they%20found%20an%20Egyptian%20man%20in%20a%20field%20and%20brought%20him%20to%20David.%20They%20gave%20him%20some%20bread%20to%20eat%20and%20water%20to%20drink.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_30_12%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2F